Growing up in the 90s and early 2Ks, I remember watching Disney movies like this all the time! This is a great disney classic from the early 2Ks. One of my favorite movies, I enjoy the nostalgia of watching these movies and the memories it brings back! The movie focuses around a group of teenagers who set out to save a Dad from a company using illegal testing and plans to use it on the Dad. Full of fun and comedy, this movie offers lessons in friendship, family, and loyalty. A great movie for all ages!
Seems like a pretty dumb movie to me but my younger brother and sister love this movie. They spent years laughing and quoting this movie.

If you type in Patrik Ian Polk's name on Amazon this film comes up. This is NOT Patrik Ian Polk's film of the same name which as of this date has not yet been released on DVD. Amazon should correct the listing, but in the meantime, be aware this is not director Polk's film. The one star is for the mistaken listing, not for this film which I have never seen.

I watched this movie for the first time when I was probably ten years old. Now, at age 23, it is still a movie I remember fondly. I don't know if I'd recommend it for someone in my age range now but I'd definitely recommended it for younger audiences who are looking for adventure, humor, and suspense. I think it was the perfect mixture.
